üéØ GOAL
Original	Alias (Used Everywhere)
username	name
phone_number	mobile

We will apply every type of alias PHP offers to this.

üü¢ 1Ô∏è‚É£ DATA MAPPING ALIAS (Application Level)

Convert field names once ‚Üí use everywhere.

process.php
session_start();

$_SESSION['name']   = $_POST['username'];      // alias
$_SESSION['mobile'] = $_POST['phone_number'];  // alias


‚úî This is logical alias
‚úî Used in real projects

üü¢ 2Ô∏è‚É£ VARIABLE REFERENCE ALIAS (&)

Make alias variables pointing to session data.

home.php
session_start();

$name   = &$_SESSION['name'];     // alias reference
$mobile = &$_SESSION['mobile'];

$name = "Updated Nambi";  // Changes session too


Now all pages see updated value.

üü¢ 3Ô∏è‚É£ ARRAY KEY ALIAS

Create a mapping array.

$fieldAlias = [
    'username' => 'name',
    'phone_number' => 'mobile'
];

$user[$fieldAlias['username']] = $_POST['username'];
$user[$fieldAlias['phone_number']] = $_POST['phone_number'];


Change alias in one place ‚Üí whole project updates.

üü¢ 4Ô∏è‚É£ OBJECT PROPERTY ALIAS

Use object to standardize names.

class User {
    public $name;
    public $mobile;

    function __construct($data) {
        $this->name   = $data['username'];      // alias
        $this->mobile = $data['phone_number'];  // alias
    }
}

$user = new User($_POST);

üü¢ 5Ô∏è‚É£ FUNCTION NAME ALIAS

Create wrapper function.

function getName() {
    return $_SESSION['name'];
}

function getMobile() {
    return $_SESSION['mobile'];
}


Now pages use:

echo getName();
echo getMobile();

üü¢ 6Ô∏è‚É£ DATABASE ALIAS
SELECT username AS name, phone_number AS mobile FROM users;


PHP side:

echo $row['name'];
echo $row['mobile'];

üü¢ 7Ô∏è‚É£ NAMESPACE / CLASS ALIAS
use App\Models\User as UserModel;

$user = new UserModel($_POST);
